{"post_content":"<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 1 \u2013 Foundations of DevOps, Containers &amp; Kubernetes<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 1: Introduction to DevOps<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is DevOps, and why does it matter?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Key DevOps principles (CI\/CD, Infrastructure as Code, automation)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>DevOps workflows and Kubernetes in the DevOps ecosystem<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 2: Docker Refresher<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding Docker containers<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Writing efficient <strong>Dockerfiles<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The Docker <strong>build process<\/strong> and caching<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Best practices<\/strong> for containerized applications<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Docker registries<\/strong> (Docker Hub, Harbor)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Introduction to <strong>docker-compose<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Building and running a multi-container application<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 3: Kubernetes Introduction<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Kubernetes, and why use it?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Kubernetes architecture: Control plane, nodes, kubelet, etcd<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Kubernetes objects and YAML basics<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Complete deployment of a sample application with Helm<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 2 \u2013 Kubernetes Deep Dive<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 4: Understanding Kubernetes Core Concepts<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Namespaces<\/strong>: Organizing Kubernetes environments<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>YAML &amp; Kinds<\/strong>: Understanding Kubernetes resource definitions<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Pods<\/strong>: The fundamental Kubernetes workload unit<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Services<\/strong>: Exposing applications inside and outside the cluster<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Multi-container Pods<\/strong>: Init containers &amp; sidecars<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Deployments<\/strong>: Managing application lifecycles<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rolling updates &amp; rollbacks<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 5: Managing Kubernetes Workloads<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Resource limits &amp; requests<\/strong>: Managing CPU &amp; memory<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Probes<\/strong>: Liveness, readiness, and startup probes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>ConfigMaps &amp; Secrets<\/strong>: Managing configurations securely<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Networking in Kubernetes<\/strong>: Cluster networking, CNI plugins<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Persistent Volumes (PV) &amp; Persistent Volume Claims (PVC)<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Deploying applications with advanced resource configurations<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 3 \u2013 Helm, Advanced Kubernetes &amp; Security<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 6: Helm \u2013 Kubernetes Package Management<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Helm, and why use it?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Writing and managing Helm charts<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using Helm templates and values<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Deploying applications with Helm<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Packaging and deploying a custom Helm chart<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 7: Helm Security \u2013 Using SOPS<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Secure management of Helm values<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Introduction to <strong>SOPS<\/strong> (Secrets OPerationS) for encrypting values<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Using SOPS to manage Kubernetes secrets securely<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 8: Advanced Kubernetes (Time Permitting)<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>StatefulSets<\/strong>: Managing stateful applications<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Jobs &amp; CronJobs<\/strong>: Running batch and scheduled workloads<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Security &amp; RBAC<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Service accounts and network policies<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Scheduling<\/strong>: Pod scheduling strategies and node affinity<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Configuring RBAC and secure workloads in Kubernetes<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Hands-on Labs &amp; Final Project<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 1<\/strong>: Writing and deploying a Dockerized application<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 2<\/strong>: Creating Kubernetes YAML manifests for various resources<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 3<\/strong>: Deploying and managing applications with Helm<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 4<\/strong>: Securing Kubernetes secrets with SOPS<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Final Project<\/strong>: Deploying and managing a production-grade application on Kubernetes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->","post_type":"training","post_status":"publish","post_name":"kubernetes-essentials","post_title":"Kubernetes Essentials","post_password":"","post_date":"2025-02-22 10:24:22","post_date_gmt":"2025-02-22 10:24:22","post_excerpt":"This 3-day hands-on training provides a comprehensive introduction to Kubernetes, from foundational concepts to advanced deployment strategies. Participants will learn how to containerize applications, manage workloads efficiently, and leverage Kubernetes for scalable infrastructure. The course covers Docker fundamentals, Helm, and best practices for securing and optimizing Kubernetes environments.","post_parent":null,"author":"admin","meta":{"_aioseo_description":[null],"_aioseo_keywords":["a:0:{}"],"_aioseo_og_article_section":[""],"_aioseo_og_article_tags":["a:0:{}"],"_aioseo_og_description":[null],"_aioseo_og_title":[null],"_aioseo_title":[null],"_aioseo_twitter_description":[null],"_aioseo_twitter_title":[null],"_edit_last":"admin","audience":["<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\r\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>DevOps engineers and system administrators<\/li>\r\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>Developers deploying applications in Kubernetes<\/li>\r\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>IT professionals managing clo